cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the issue of bias in machine learning models, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the challenge of collecting labeled data, which is relevant to the subfield of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social computing (cs.SI). Finally, the proposed solution of fair active learning could also be applicable to the subfield of control and optimization (cs.CY) in order to balance model performance and fairness.
